{
  "texts": [
    "To systematically evaluate this challenge, project-level benchmarks such as ProjectTest have been proposed.",
    "Studies on these benchmarks show that even when provided with full project code, LLMs still struggle to understand project structure and dependencies, leading to numerous basic compilation and import errors [142].Limited Comprehension Capability.",
    "While LLMs excel at understanding general coding patterns, their insufficient understanding of complex logic and domain-specific knowledge limits their effectiveness on non-trivial software.",
    "This is evident in several aspects.",
    "To begin with, test coverage drops significantly for modules with complex nested logic, state transitions, or temporal dependencies."
  ]
}